article.headline: Bethune-Cookman 52, Stetson 51
article.story: DAYTONA BEACH, Fla. (AP) -- Jimmy Hudson had a game high 20 points, including a baseline jumper with 28.4 seconds remaining, to give Bethune-Cookman a 52-51 win over Stetson on Monday night. Hudson's final basket gave Bethune-Cookman a 3 point lead, 52-49. Stetson's Eric Diaz closed the margin to 1 on a layup with 7.8 seconds left, but neither team could score again. Bethune-Cookman (3-4) scored 12 straight points during a six-minute stretch in the second half, giving the Rattlers a 42-32 lead with 9:05 remaining. Hudson had 6 points during the run. Stetson (2-7), paced by A.J. Smith's 14 points, began closing the gap. A pair of quick 3-pointers by Mark Lohuis narrowed it to 2 points, 49-47, with 4:32 left. Stetson (2-7) never led in the second half. The most the Hatters led by was 4 early in the game when the score was 7-3. The lead changed hands 11 times before halftime, when Bethune-cookman took a 26-25 lead. A.J. Smith led Stetson with 14 points.
